- Always use null-safety and follow Effective Dart.
- Prefer small widgets, extract private widgets when build() grows.
- When changing UI, keep existing behavior unless explicitly asked.
- Always update or create tests when adding logic (unit/widget tests).
- Prefer const constructors where possible.
- Use Theme.of(context) and avoid hardcoded colors/sizes when feasible.
- Do not introduce new state management libs unless asked.
- When editing pubspec.yaml, explain why each dependency is needed.
- Output: provide code changes with file paths and minimal explanation.
- The architecture this project is Clean architecture